        <abstract>
            <p>Evidence for inheritance of constitutional diseases like scrofula so good that it seems rash to breed tainted animal.</p> 
<p>Experiments given in <hi rend="italic">Cross and self-fertilisation</hi> show that evil of inbreeding follows from near relations possessing closely similar constitution.</p> 
            <p>Size and vigour increased by breeding plants and animals from ancestors that lived some generations under different conditions of life.</p>
        </abstract>
